    =image_tag("icons/22x22/grid.png", :border => 0)
    =@title
  %center
    %table#invheaders_demo0402.scroll{ :cellspacing => "0", :cellpadding => "0" }
    #invheaders_demo0402_pager.scroll{ :style => "text-align:center;" }
/ End demo
.demo-description
  %p
    This example demonstrates using a subgrid with JSON Data. To the subgrid url is passed the id
    of the row. If there is a need to pass another parameters to subgrid url that are part of the
    grid data a params array can be constructed.
  %p
    Example: if we want to pass the date too - the
    subGridModel can look like this:
    %code
      %br
      \...
      %br
      subGridModel: [{ name  : ['No','Item','Qty','Unit','Line Total'],
      %br
      width : [55,200,80,80,80],
      %br
      params: ['invdate']}
      %br
      \...
  %p
    where the 'invdate' is a valid name from colModel. And a parameter invdate='xxxxx' is
    constructed.
/ End demo-description
